til the arrival of medical assistance.</p>                          <p>This course teaches special techniques for children and infants so is ideal for new mums and all parents who want to be prepared with the skills and confidence to respond without hesitation in the case of an emergency</p>                        </div>                     </div>                      <div class=\"panel-heading\">                       <h4 class=\"panel-title\">                         <a data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-parent=\"#accordion_single\" href=\"#collapse2\" class=\"show_plus\"><i class=\"more-less glyphicon glyphicon-plus\"></i> Pre-Requisites/Entry Requirements </a>                       </h4>                     </div>                     <div id=\"collapse2\" class=\"panel-collapse collapse in\">                       <div class=\"panel-body\">                         <ul class=\"Listing_view\">                             <li>There are no qualification pre-requisites for this course</li>                             <li>Learners must be aged 16 years or older</li>                             <li>Photo Identification is required to be sited prior to course commencement</li>                             <li>Language, literacy and numeracy skills</li>                             <li>Learners must be physically capable of bending and kneeling to provide first aid to a person on the floor. This includes performing CPR for up to 5 minutes.</li>                             <li>Completed enrolment form</li>                             <li>Payment of the course cost</li>                           </ul>                       </div>                     </div>                      <div class=\"panel-heading\">                       <h4 class=\"panel-title\">                         <a data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-parent=\"#accordion_single\" href=\"#collapse3\" class=\"show_plus\"><i class=\"more-less glyphicon glyphicon-plus\"></i> Mode of Delivery </a>                       </h4> 