pplication of knowledge. The assessment will also be part of a simulated activity set by the assessor. This activity must be conducted by an assessor or Optimistic Futures and must be completed in the workplace or in another environment that accurately simulates the workplace. The assessor is too actively set tasks for the student and must observe these tasks being performed.</p>                            <p>To standardise the application of the assessment, the assessment tasks (required skills and knowledge) are based on those specified in the Unit of Competency, HLTAID002- Emergency First Aid The assessor will use an assessment instrument mapped accordingly to the assessment requirements of this unit of competency. Assessors will apply an assessment procedure to ensure you are ready for the assessment and have the right resources and equipment to achieve the right standard.</p>                       </div>                     </div>                        <div class=\"panel-heading\">                       <h4 class=\"panel-title\">                         <a data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-parent=\"#accordion_single\" href=\"#collapse9\" class=\"show_plus\"><i class=\"more-less glyphicon glyphicon-plus\"></i> Course Topics </a>                       </h4>                     </div>                     <div id=\"collapse9\" class=\"panel-collapse collapse in\">                       <div class=\"panel-body\">                                                  <ul class=\"Listing_view\">                           <li>The DRSABCD Action Plan</li>                           <li>Managing unconscious casualties</li>                           <li>Cardiopulmonary Resuscitation (CPR)</li>                           <li>Using on Automated External Defibrillator</li>                           <li>Legal issues</li>                           <li>Infection controls</li>                           <li>Choking</li>                           <li>Heart attack</li>                       