 be completed in the workplace or in another environment that accurately simulates the workplace. The assessor is too actively set tasks for the student and must observe these tasks being performed.</p>                            <p>To standardise the application of the assessment, the assessment tasks (required skills and knowledge) are based on those specified in the Unit of Competency, HLTAID003- Provide First Aid The assessor will use an assessment instrument mapped accordingly to the assessment requirements of this unit of competency. Assessors will apply an assessment procedure to ensure you are ready for the assessment and have the right resources and equipment to achieve the right standard.</p>                       </div>                     </div>                        <div class=\"panel-heading\">                       <h4 class=\"panel-title\">                         <a data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-parent=\"#accordion_single\" href=\"#collapse9\" class=\"show_plus\"><i class=\"more-less glyphicon glyphicon-plus\"></i> Course Topics </a>                       </h4>                     </div>                     <div id=\"collapse9\" class=\"panel-collapse collapse in\">                       <div class=\"panel-body\">                                                  <ul class=\"Listing_view\">                             <li>The DRSABCD Action Plan</li>                             <li>Managing unconscious casualties</li>                             <li>Cardiopulmonary Resuscitation (CPR)</li>                             <li>Using on External Automated Defibrillator (AED)</li>                             <li>Legal issues</li>                             <li>Infection controls</li>                             <li>Choking</li>                             <li>Heart attack</li>                             <li>Asthma</li>                             <li>Anaphylaxis</li>                             <li>Wounds and bleeding</li>                         </ul>                        </div>                     </div>                      <div class=\"panel-heading\">                       <h4 class=\"panel-title\">                         <a data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-parent=\"#accordion_single\" href=\"#collapse10\" class=\"show_plus\"><i class=\"more-less glyphicon glyphicon-plus\"></i> National Recognition </a>                       </h4>                     </div>                     <div id=\"collapse10\" class=\"panel-collapse collapse in\">                       <div class=\"panel-body\">                        <p>A certificate will be awarded upon successful completion of the unit; HLTAID003- Provide First Aid</p>                          <p>This unit of competence is nationally recognised and provides individuals with a valuable outcome that can be applied throughout Australia.</p>                       </div>                     </div>                        <div class=\"panel-heading\">                       <h4 class=\"panel-title\">                         <a data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-parent=\"#accordion_single\" href=\"#collapse10\" class=\"show_plus\"><i class=\"more-less glyphicon glyphicon-plus\"></i> Fees and Charges </a>                       </h4>                     </div>                     <div id=\"collapse10\" class=\"panel-collapse collapse in\">                       <div class=\"panel-body\">                        <p>Information about fees and charges is provided in the schedule of fees and charges which will have been included in your pre-enrolment information package. The basic course fees are: $65 per person.</p>                       </div>                     </div>                       <div class=\"panel-heading\">                       <h4 class=\"panel-title\">                         <a data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-parent=\"#accordion_single\" href=\"#collapse12\" class=\"show_plus\"><i class=\"more-less glyphicon glyphicon-plus\"></i> Payment method </a>                       </h4>                     </div>                     <div id=\"collapse12\" class=\"panel-collapse collapse in\">                       <div class=\"panel-body\">                         <p>TEftpos and Cash</p>                       </div>                     </div>                       <div class=\"panel-heading\">                       <h4 class=\"panel-title\">                         <a data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-parent=\"#accordion_single\" href=\"#collapse13\" class=\"show_plus\"><i class=\"more-less glyphicon glyphicon-plus\"></i> We also deliver the following courses </a>                       </h4>                     </div>                     <div id=\"collapse13\" class=\"panel-collapse collapse in\">                       <div class=\"panel-body\">                         <ul class=\"Listing_view\">                           <li>CHC30113- Certificate III in Early Childhood Education and Care</li>                           <li>CHC50113- Diploma of Early Childhood Education and Care</li>                           <li>CPP20212- Certificate II in Security Operations</li>                           <li>CPP30411- Certificate III in Security Operations</li>                         </ul>                       </div>                     </div>                       <div class=\"panel-heading\">                       <h4 class=\"panel-title\">                         <a data-toggle=\"collapse\" data-parent=\"#accordion_single\" href=\"#collapse14\" class=\"show_plus\"><i class=\"more-less glyphicon glyphicon-plus\"></i> Responsibility for Training </a>                       </h4>                     </div>                     <div id=\"collapse14\" class=\"panel-collapse collapse in\">                       <div class=\"panel-body\">                         <p>Optimistic Futures is responsible for the quality and delivery of training and assessment and will be the organisation issuing any qualification and statements of attainment to eligible students, upon su